I

ImageCreature - Class in aquarium.creatures
A Creature which can be given the name of a file residing in "aquarium\images" and will use that image file as the appearance.

L

LineSwimmer - Class in aquarium.creatures
A LineSwimmer is an ImageCreature which: Moves at a given whole integer slope speed, in a straight line; Bounces off of the walls, the floor, and the surface of the water, in order to stay underwater.
LineSwimmer(String, String, int) - Constructor for class aquarium.creatures.LineSwimmer
Creates a LineSwimmer.

U

updateCreatureLocations() - Method in class aquarium.Aquarium
Calls the Creature.updateLocation() method for each Creature in the Aquarium, and then calls: Creature.hitLeftWall() if the left edge of the Creature has touched or gone past the left wall; Creature.hitRightWall() if the right edge of the Creature has touched or gone past the right wall; Creature.hitFloor() if the bottom edge of the Creature has touched or gone past the Aquarium floor; Creature.hitSurface() if the Creature is touching the surface of the water; Creature.hitClouds() if the Creature has touched or gone past the top of the sky.
updateLocation() - Method in interface aquarium.creatures.Creature
Causes the Creature to move in some way.
updateLocation() - Method in class aquarium.creatures.ImageCreature
 
updateLocation() - Method in class aquarium.creatures.LineSwimmer
Moves the LineSwimmer in the amount of its given speed in both the X and Y directions.
